name: Vitelcom Cellular DBA Innovative Wireless
technicalcomment:
Vitelcom (Viya) is a child company of Commnet and share the same realm with Commnet.
Viya uses the Commnet realm and a subset of the Commnet IMSI prefix for diameter routing. 

As TotalVis customer, Commnet wish to see which traffic belongs to them (parent company) and which traffic belongs to Viya.

From a diameter route election perspective, Viya will not have access to elect routes and would only ¡°inherit¡± Commnet¡¯s roaming relationships.

From a diameter routing perspective, the NA DSCs will route messages from IMSI prefix 3110405, destined toward Commnets realm via the Viya peer connections. All other IMSI prefixes 311040(0-4) & 311040(6-9) destined toward Commnet¡¯s realm will be routed via the Commnet peer connections.
